==German==
===Etymology===
Old High German ''daz'', originally [[dat]]
===Article===
{{German definite article}}
'''das'''
*Nominative singular neuter of the [[definite article]]. See ''[[der]]''.

===Relative pronoun===
'''das'''
# In a subordinate clause, indicates a person or thing referenced in the main clause.  Used with neuter singular referents.
#: Ich kenne ein M&auml;dchen, ''das'' das kann: I know a girl ''who'' can do that.

====Translations====

*[[English]]: [[who]], [[that]]

